@node "Req" "Requirements"

REQUIREMENTS:

Any AMIGA with 1MB RAM, ROM 2.04 or higher and PAL Monitor or TV.
The asl.library in your LIBS: Dir. (Not distributed with AmigaTEd)
Topaz.font in your FONTS: Dir. (Not distributed with AmigaTEd)

The program works fine in ALL AMIGA computers. Also you can
load and use the program if you have an NTSC Monitor.

This program has been developed with my A500, 68000@7MHz, 1MB CHIP RAM,
4MB FAST RAM, ROM 3.1, 210MB HD and 1084S monitor.

This program ( or previous versions ) has been tested on this machines:

-A plain A1200 with 8MB RAM
-A1200 68030 28 MHZ 18MB RAM ROM 3.0
-A4000 68030 25 MHZ 10MB RAM ROM 3.0

Also tested with some System patches.
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"

USAGE:

To load the program, double-click on the AmigaTEd icon.
When the program is loaded you can see two different zones:
A zone with some buttons: (From left to right)
             - Load Text
             - Open a Shell
             - Top of Document
             - Save Text
             - Save As
             - Bottom of text
             - Print Text
             - About Requester
             - Put current hour in text
             - Clear ALL Text
             - Start of line
             - Insert Line
             - Delete Line
             - End of line
             - Screen To Back
             - Quit program

The other zone is the Text Zone.

SHORTCUT KEYS:

AmigaTEd V4.8 no have menus. You can access to all functions
in AmigaTEd using buttons or Shortcut Keys.
This is a list of Shortcut Keys available in this version:

AMIGA + O  (Open text)
AMIGA + W  (Save text)
AMIGA + S  (Save As....)
AMIGA + P  (Print text)
AMIGA + A  (About requester)
AMIGA + Z  (Open Shell)
AMIGA + Q  (Quit program)
AMIGA + T  (Top of document)
AMIGA + B  (End of document)
AMIGA + L  (Insert a new line)
AMIGA + K  (Delete line)
AMIGA + D  (Delete the whole text)
AMIGA + 0  (Start of line)
AMIGA + 1  (End of line)
AMIGA + Y  (Insert date (MM/DD/YY format) in text)
AMIGA + H  (Insert current time in text)

How to COPY and PASTE text:
Doubleclick on the line you want to copy. Then put the cursor where
do you want to paste and press RIGHT mouse button. Easy to copy and
paste.

HINTS: 
If you want to go to the end of a very long line, click with mouse
on and use the Horizontal Slider or the button for this action.
@endnode

@node "NewI" "Changes"

What's new in AmigaTEd V4.8 :

- Copy and Paste functions added.
- Added a quit requester (You can quit the program directly using
                          AMIGA + Q)
@endnode

